    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-08-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="173"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d173">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4002/223–225.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Chargé <persName type="to">Fletcher</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-08-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 12, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 619.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    1198 of the 3d ultimo, regarding the municipal administration of places along
                    the line of the Chinese Eastern Railway, and inclosing a copy of the note
                    addressed to the Wai-wu Pu by you on June 23, 1909.</p>
                <p>The department has read your dispatch with interest and approves your note to the
                    Wai-wu Pu and the verbal statement which you report having made to the Russian
                    minister as to the objections of this Government to the new agreement.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
